<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin adjective 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. Lin &amp; S. Li" authorityYear="2020" class="Arachnida" family="Symphytognathidae" genus="Crassignatha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="rostriformis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rostriformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">rostriformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(rostriform), in reference to the shape of the copulatory openings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
